HELP VIEWER
===========
- Ctrl+g y opens this file in less.
- Press / to search, n/N for next/previous match, q to quit.

TMUX / PSMUX LOCK/UNLOCK KEYBINDS (mirrors the Zellij lock/unlock config)
==========================================================================

Prefix is Ctrl+g — the same gate key used in the Zellij lock/unlock config,
for identical muscle memory across both tools. Unlike the old hybrid layer,
there is no separate "no-prefix Alt layer" here except one deliberate
exception: Ctrl+Alt+hjkl for pane focus (same exception made in Zellij).
Ctrl+Alt (not plain Alt) per herdr's own vetted-safe recommendation: the
only modifier family left untouched by every terminal/OS combination tested.

tmux's own prefix mechanism already reverts to passthrough after one
keystroke natively — you never "stay" in a captured state, no lock toggle
needed for one-shot actions.

Friendly help
-------------
Ctrl+g y                 Open this cheatsheet
Ctrl+g Y                 Show raw tmux/psmux key table

No-prefix exception (Ctrl+Alt, mirrors Zellij's one exception)
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Ctrl+Alt+h/j/k/l              Focus pane left/down/up/right
Ctrl+Alt+Left/Down/Up/Right   Focus pane left/down/up/right

Everything else below requires Ctrl+g first.

Panes behind prefix (Ctrl+g)
-----------------------------
Focus / selection
Ctrl+g h/j/k/l           Focus pane left/down/up/right (repeatable via repeat-time)

Pane management
Ctrl+g s                 New pane, smart split on the longest axis
Ctrl+g d                 New pane, split down (also Ctrl+g " [tmux default] and Ctrl+g - [herdr default])
Ctrl+g r                 New pane, split right (also Ctrl+g % [tmux default] and Ctrl+g v [herdr default])
                         (no "stacked" bind — tmux has no stacked-pane layout)
Ctrl+g x                 Close pane (asks y/n confirmation)
Ctrl+g z                 Toggle pane zoom/fullscreen
Ctrl+g f                 Floating-ish popup shell
Ctrl+g t                 Rename pane (sets pane title, prompts for text; mnemonic: Title)

Resize — sticky table (Ctrl+g then Ctrl+r)
------------------------------------------------
Ctrl+g Ctrl+r            Enter the Resize table (mnemonic: r = Resize)
  h/j/k/l or arrows        Resize left/down/up/right by 3, repeats without prefix
  Esc / Enter / q          Exit back to normal typing

Move — sticky table (Ctrl+g m)
---------------------------------
Ctrl+g m                 Enter the Move table
  h/j/k/l or arrows        Swap focused pane with the one in that direction
  Esc / Enter / m          Exit back to normal typing

Tabs (tmux windows) behind prefix
------------------------------------
Ctrl+g c                 New tab/window (tmux-vanilla mnemonic: Create)
Ctrl+g ,  / Ctrl+g p     Previous tab (two aliases)
Ctrl+g .  / Ctrl+g n     Next tab (two aliases, tmux-vanilla n/p mnemonic)
Ctrl+g 1..9              Go to tab 1..9
Ctrl+g Shift+t           Close tab/window
Ctrl+g Shift+r           Rename tab/window (prompts for text)
Ctrl+g i                 Move tab left
Ctrl+g o                 Move tab right

Layouts behind prefix
------------------------
Ctrl+g [                 Previous layout
Ctrl+g ]                 Next layout

Session / client behind prefix
------------------------------
Ctrl+g w                 Session manager (choose-tree)
Ctrl+g Shift+d           Detach client
Ctrl+g Ctrl+s            Enter copy-mode (scroll/search)
Ctrl+g Ctrl+q            Kill current session (WITH confirmation — a real dialog,
                         which the Zellij side does not have natively)

Copy mode (vi) — entered via Ctrl+g Ctrl+s
--------------------------------------------
Movement
h j k l                  Left / down / up / right
w b e                    Word motions
0 ^ $                    Start / first nonblank / end of line
g / G                    Top / bottom of scrollback
Ctrl+u / Ctrl+d          Half page up / down
Ctrl+b / Ctrl+f          Full page up / down
PageUp / PageDown        Full page up / down

Search
/                        Search forward
?                        Search backward
n / N                    Next / previous match

Selection / copy
Space                    Start selection
v / Ctrl+v               Toggle rectangle selection
V                        Line selection
y / Enter                Copy and exit
o                        Swap cursor/anchor ends
Esc / q                  Exit copy mode

Zellij <-> tmux parity (both use Ctrl+g as the gate)
--------------------------------------------------------
Matching Zellij exactly:
h/j/k/l        focus pane            (also Ctrl+Alt+hjkl, no prefix, both tools)
d/r            new pane down/right
x              close pane (tmux confirms y/n; Zellij does not)
z              fullscreen/zoom
f              floating-ish popup shell
Ctrl+r         enter sticky Resize table
m              enter sticky Move table
1-9            go to tab N
Shift+t        close tab
Shift+r        rename tab
i/o            move tab left/right
[/]            prev/next layout
w              session manager
Shift+d        detach
Ctrl+s         scroll/copy-mode
Ctrl+q         quit (tmux confirms; Zellij needs the zj-quit plugin for that)
y/Y            cheatsheet / raw keylist

Diverging on purpose (tmux-specific choices):
s              new pane smart split   (Zellij uses "s" for stacked instead)
c              new tab/window         (Zellij uses "c" for rename pane)
t              rename pane            (Zellij uses "t" for new tab)
n/p            next/previous tab, ALIAS alongside ,/. (tmux-vanilla mnemonic)

Notes
-----
- Prefix is Ctrl+g (changed from Ctrl+b/Ctrl+a in older setups).
- Ctrl+Alt combinations are the safest cross-terminal/cross-OS family (herdr's
  own vetted recommendation); if Ctrl+Alt+hjkl still misbehaves in some host
  terminal, use Ctrl+g h/j/k/l instead.
- tmux does not support stacked panes like Zellij; use split down/right instead.
